  "correctAnswer": "C",
  "section": "Math",
  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Use the vertex",
      "content": "A horizontal line $y=c$ intersects a parabola at exactly one point when it passes through the vertex. So $c$ is the vertex's $y$-coordinate."
    },
    {
      "title": "Find the vertex input",
      "content": "For $y=-x^2+7x-80$, the vertex occurs at<br/>$$x=-\\frac{b}{2a}=-\\frac{7}{2(-1)}=\\frac{7}{2}$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Evaluate the vertex",
      "content": "Substitute $x=\\frac{7}{2}$.<br/>$$c=-(\\frac{7}{2})^2+7(\\frac{7}{2})-80$$<br/>$$c=-\\frac{49}{4}+\\frac{98}{4}-\\frac{320}{4}=-\\frac{271}{4}$$<br/>The answer is <strong>C</strong>."
    }
  ]
}
